something important?

245
00:24:34,180 --> 00:24:39,300
Never. Give him a living, but never
discuss the family business with him.

246
00:24:39,380 --> 00:24:42,060
-What else?
-Virgil Sollozzo called.

247
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:46,420
-We'll have to see him next week.
-When you come back from California.

248
00:24:47,780 --> 00:24:50,740
-When am I going to California?
-Tonight.

249
00:24:50,860 --> 00:24:55,940
I want you to talk to this movie big shot
and settle this business for Johnny.

250
00:24:57,220 --> 00:25:01,220
If there's nothing else, I'd like to go
to my daughter's wedding.

251
00:25:03,300 --> 00:25:06,100
Carlo, we're going to take the picture.

252
00:25:07,140 --> 00:25:08,820
M ICHAEL: Wait a minute.

253
00:25:08,900 --> 00:25:11,140
KAY: No, Michael. Not me.

254
00:25:15,460 --> 00:25:18,180
Okay, that's it. Just like that. Hold it!

255
00:25:21,300 --> 00:25:23,220
(BAND PLAYING WALTZ)

256
00:26:52,900 --> 00:26:54,340
(BELL RINGING)

257
00:26:56,580 --> 00:26:58,340
(ALL CHATTERING)

258
00:27:03,780 --> 00:27:05,420
MAN: You need
a little more heat on that arc.

259
00:27:05,540 --> 00:27:06,820
Start talking.

260
00:27:06,900 --> 00:27:10,180
I was sent by a friend
of Johnny Fontane.

261
00:27:10,260 --> 00:27:13,860
This friend would give
his friendship to Mr. Woltz,

262
00:27:13,940 --> 00:27:16,700
if Mr. Woltz would grant us a favor.

263
00:27:19,060 --> 00:27:22,980
Give Johnny the part in that war film
you're starting next week.

264
00:27:24,180 --> 00:27:25,540
(CHUCKLES)

265
00:27:28,460 --> 00:27:33,300
And what favor would your friend
grant Mr. Woltz?

266
00:27:33,380 --> 00:27:36,740
He could make your future union
problems disappear.

267
00:27:36,820 --> 00:27:40,740
And one of your stars has just moved
from marijuana to heroin.

268
00:27:40,820 --> 00:27:44,980
Are you trying to muscle me?
Listen, you son -of-a -bitch!

269
00:27:45,060 --> 00:27:47,540
Let me lay it on the line.

270
00:27:47,620 --> 00:27:49,500
Johnny Fontane
will never get that movie!

271
00:27:49,620 --> 00:27:53,980
No matter how many Dago Guinea
greaseballs come out of the woodwork!

272
00:27:54,060 --> 00:27:57,700
- German -Irish.
-Listen here, my Kraut -Mick friend.

273
00:27:57,780 --> 00:28:02,020
- going to make trouble for you!
- a lawyer. I haven't threatened...

274
00:28:02,100 --> 00:28:05,340
I know New York's big lawyers.
Who are you?

275
00:28:05,420 --> 00:28:08,820
I have a special practice.
I handle one client.

276
00:28:08,900 --> 00:28:10,820
I'll wait for your call.

277
00:28:12,460 --> 00:28:15,300
By the way,
I admire your pictures very much.

278
00:28:19,940 --> 00:28:21,380
Check him out.

279
00:28:42,980 --> 00:28:45,380
-It's really beautiful.
-Look at this.

280
00:28:45,460 --> 00:28:49,820
-It used to decorate a king's palace.
-Very nice.

281
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:52,180
WOLTZ: Why didn't you say
you work for Corleone?

282
00:28:52,300 --> 00:28:56,300
I thought you were some cheap hustler
Johnny was running in.

283
00:28:56,420 --> 00:28:59,580
-I only use his name when necessary.
-WOLTZ: How's your drink?

284
00:28:59,700 --> 00:29:03,060
-Fine.
-Now I'll show you something beautiful.

285
00:29:03,140 --> 00:29:05,580
You do appreciate beauty, don't you?

286
00:29:08,420 --> 00:29:11,380
There you are. $600 ,000 on four hoofs.

287
00:29:11,460 --> 00:29:15,260
I bet Russian czars never paid
that for a single horse.

288
00:29:15,340 --> 00:29:16,780
Khartoum.

289
00:29:17,380 --> 00:29:18,660
Khartoum.

290
00:29:20,100 --> 00:29:24,300
not going to race him, though.
going to put him out to stud.

291
00:29:25,860 --> 00:29:27,300
Thanks, Tony.

292
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:30,900
Let's get something to eat.

293
00:29:30,980 --> 00:29:34,220
TOM : Corleone is Johnny's godfather.

294
00:29:34,340 --> 00:29:38,580
To the Italian people that's
a very sacred, close relationship.

295
00:29:38,660 --> 00:29:42,380
I respect it.
Tell him to ask me anything else.

296
00:29:42,500 --> 00:29:44,740
This favor I can't give him.

297
00:29:44,820 --> 00:29:47,980
He never asks a second favor
when he's been refused the first.

298
00:29:48,100 --> 00:29:53,980
You don't understand.
Johnny Fontane never gets that movie.

299
00:29:54,060 --> 00:29:57,580
That part is perfect for him.
It'll make him a big star.

300
00:29:57,700 --> 00:30:01,620
going to run him out of the business,
and let me tell you why.

301
00:30:03,540 --> 00:30:08,060
Johnny Fontane ruined one of Woltz
International's most valuable protégés.

302
00:30:08,140 --> 00:30:13,260
We trained her for five years.
Singing, acting, dancing lessons.

303
00:30:13,380 --> 00:30:17,820
I spent hundreds of thousands of dollars
on her , to make her a big star.

304
00:30:17,900 --> 00:30:20,580
Let me be even more frank.

305
00:30:20,660 --> 00:30:25,420
To show you that  not a hard -hearted
man. That it's not all dollars and cents.

306
00:30:25,540 --> 00:30:29,020
She was beautiful.
She was young and innocent!

307
00:30:29,100 --> 00:30:34,260
She's the greatest piece of ass I've had
and I've had them all over the world.

308
00:30:34,340 --> 00:30:40,260
Then Johnny Fontane comes along with
his olive oil voice and Guinea charm.

309
00:30:40,340 --> 00:30:41,940
And she runs off.

310
00:30:43,220 --> 00:30:47,180
She threw it all away
just to make me look ridiculous!

311
00:30:47,300 --> 00:30:52,220
And a man in my position can't afford
to be made to look ridiculous!

312
00:30:52,300 --> 00:30:54,540
You get the hell out of here!

313
00:30:54,660 --> 00:30:58,820
If that goombah tries any rough stuff,
tell him  no bandleader.

314
00:31:00,020 --> 00:31:02,900
Yeah, I heard that story.

315
00:31:03,780 --> 00:31:07,620
Thank you for dinner
and a very pleasant evening.

316
00:31:07,700 --> 00:31:10,420
Maybe your car can take me
to the airport.

317
00:31:10,500 --> 00:31:13,940
Mr. Corleone insists on hearing
bad news immediately.

318
00:32:38,180 --> 00:32:39,740
(WOLTZ SCREAM ING)

319
00:32:47,740 --> 00:32:49,460
(SCREAM ING CONTINUES)

320
00:33:01,980 --> 00:33:05,740
-You're not too tired, are you, Tom?
-No, I slept on the plane.

321
00:33:05,820 --> 00:33:08,780
I have the Sollozzo notes here.

322
00:33:08,860 --> 00:33:10,060
Now...

323
00:33:11,980 --> 00:33:15,420
Sollozzo is known as The Turk.

324
00:33:15,500 --> 00:33:17,380
He's supposed to be very good
with a knife,

325
00:33:17,460 --> 00:33:21,700
<i>but only in matters of business
with reasonable complaint.</i>

326
00:33:21,780 --> 00:33:24,900
<i>His business is narcotics.</i>

327
00:33:24,980 --> 00:33:28,220
<i>He has fields in Turkey,
where they grow poppy.</i>

328
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:31,980
<i>In Sicily he has plants
to process them into heroin.</i>

329
00:33:32,060 --> 00:33:35,460
<i>He needs cash,
he needs protection from the police.</i>

330
00:33:35,540 --> 00:33:39,260
<i>He'll give a piece of the action.
I don't know how much.</i>

331
00:33:39,380 --> 00:33:44,380
<i>The Tattaglia family is behind him here.
They have to be in it for something.</i>

332
00:33:45,620 --> 00:33:50,020
-What about his prison record?
-One term in Italy, one here.

333
00:33:50,100 --> 00:33:52,740
He's known as a top narcotics man.

334
00:33:52,820 --> 00:33:57,300
-Santino, what do you think?
-A lot of money in that white powder.

335
00:33:59,540 --> 00:34:00,860
Tom?

336
00:34:00,940 --> 00:34:04,940
<i>TOM: Yes. There's more money
in narcotics than anything else.</i>

337
00:34:05,020 --> 00:34:09,580
<i>If we don't get into it, somebody else
will, maybe the five families.</i>

338
00:34:09,660 --> 00:34:13,940
With that money they can buy
more police and political power.

339
00:34:14,020 --> 00:34:16,020
Then they come after us.

340
00:34:16,140 --> 00:34:22,380
Now we have unions and gambling, and
that's great¤, but narcotics is the future.

341
00:34:22,460 --> 00:34:27,340
If we don't get a piece of that action,
we risk everything in 10 years' time.

342
00:34:31,700 --> 00:34:34,660
So? What's your answer
going to be, Pop?

343
00:34:39,220 --> 00:34:40,900
Don Corleone.

344
00:34:42,900 --> 00:34:46,060
I need a man who has powerful friends.

345
00:34:46,180 --> 00:34:48,780
I need a million dollars in cash.

346
00:34:48,860 --> 00:34:54,460
I need those politicians that you carry
in your pocket, like nickels and dimes.

347
00:34:55,860 --> 00:34:59,740
-What is the interest for my family?
-30%.

348
00:34:59,820 --> 00:35:03,620
In the first year your end should be
three, four million dollars.

349
00:35:03,700 --> 00:35:05,580
And then it would go up.

350
00:35:06,740 --> 00:35:10,020
And what is the interest
for the Tattaglia family?

351
00:35:11,940 --> 00:35:13,700
My compliments.

352
00:35:17,260 --> 00:35:20,540
I'll take care of them, out of my share.

353
00:35:20,620 --> 00:35:24,700
So I receive 30% for finance,

354
00:35:24,820 --> 00:35:28,020
political influence and legal protection?

355
00:35:28,100 --> 00:35:29,700
That's right.

356
00:35:30,940 --> 00:35:34,740
Why do you come to me?
Why do I deserve this generosity?

357
00:35:34,820 --> 00:35:39,900
If you consider a million dollars in cash
just finance,

358
00:35:39,980 --> 00:35:42,060
te salud, Don Corleone.

359
00:35:52,140 --> 00:35:57,140
I said that I would see you, because
I heard you were a serious man,

360
00:35:57,220 --> 00:35:59,380
to be treated with respect.

361
00:36:03,860 --> 00:36:07,060
But, I must say no to you.

362
00:36:08,180 --> 00:36:10,900
And I'll give you my reason.

363
00:36:10,980 --> 00:36:13,660
It's true,
I have a lot of friends in politics.

364
00:36:14,900 --> 00:36:19,140
They wouldn't be friendly long if I was
involved in drugs instead of gambling,

365
00:36:19,220 --> 00:36:24,620
which they regard as a harmless vice,
but drugs is a dirty business.

366
00:36:24,700 --> 00:36:29,460
It doesn't make any difference to me
what a man does for a living.

367
00:36:29,540 --> 00:36:34,580
But your business is...a little dangerous.

368
00:36:34,660 --> 00:36:38,940
If you're worried about security,
the Tattaglias will guarantee it.

369
00:36:39,020 --> 00:36:42,380
-The Tattaglias would guarantee our...
-Wait a minute.

370
00:36:49,340 --> 00:36:53,980
I have a sentimental weakness
for my children, and I spoil them.

371
00:36:54,060 --> 00:36:57,140
They talk when they should listen.
But anyway...

372
00:36:57,260 --> 00:37:02,420
Signor Sollozzo, my no is final. I wish to
congratulate you on your new business.

373
00:37:02,500 --> 00:37:05,820
I know you'll do well, and good luck.

374
00:37:05,900 --> 00:37:10,540
Especially since your interests
don't conflict with mine. Thank you.

375
00:37:30,340 --> 00:37:32,180
Santino.

376
00:37:32,260 --> 00:37:34,020
Come here.

377
00:37:36,220 --> 00:37:38,060
What's the matter with you?

378
00:37:38,140 --> 00:37:42,620
Your brain is going soft
from playing with that girl.

379
00:37:42,700 --> 00:37:46,620
Never tell anybody outside the family
what you're thinking again.

380
00:37:47,860 --> 00:37:49,100
Go on.

381
00:37:52,900 --> 00:37:55,620
Tom, what's this nonsense?

382
00:37:55,700 --> 00:37:58,940
It's from Johnny.
He's starring in that new film.

383
00:38:01,220 --> 00:38:03,660
-Take it away.
-Take it over there.

384
00:38:04,900 --> 00:38:06,380
And

385
00:38:07,340 --> 00:38:09,420
tell Luca Brasi to come in.

386
00:38:15,380 --> 00:38:18,660
a little worried
about this Sollozzo fellow.

387
00:38:18,740 --> 00:38:21,580
Find out what he's got
under his fingernails.

388
00:38:22,540 --> 00:38:26,020
Go to the Tattaglias.

389
00:38:26,100 --> 00:38:30,220
Make them think that you're not
too happy with our family

390
00:38:31,540 --> 00:38:33,820
and find out what you can.

391
00:38:50,580 --> 00:38:53,740
I got something for your mother
and for Sonny

392
00:38:53,820 --> 00:38:58,300
and a tie for Freddy,
and Tom Hagen got the Reynolds pen.

393
00:38:58,380 --> 00:39:01,500
-What do you want for Christmas?
-Just you.

394
00:39:03,380 --> 00:39:06,780
<i>(HAVE YOURSELF A MERRY LITTLE
CHRISTMAS PLAYING ON RADIO)</i>

395
00:39:32,060 --> 00:39:33,980
VITO: Andiamo, Fredo.

396
00:39:34,060 --> 00:39:37,340
-Tell Paulie to get the car.
-Okay, Pop.

397
00:39:37,420 --> 00:39:41,180
I'll have to get it myself.
Paulie called in sick this morning.

398
00:39:42,900 --> 00:39:46,020
Paulie's a good kid.
I don't mind getting the car.

399
00:39:49,300 --> 00:39:51,380
<i>Buon natale, Caro. Gràzie.</i>

400
00:40:32,260 --> 00:40:36,380
-Luca!  Bruno Tattaglia.
-I know.

401
00:40:37,380 --> 00:40:39,180
(BOTH SPEAKING ITALIAN)

402
00:40:45,820 --> 00:40:46,860
You know who I am?

403
00:40:46,940 --> 00:40:48,220
(IN ITALIAN) I know you.

404
00:40:49,460 --> 00:40:52,900
(IN ITALIAN) You have been talking
to the Tattaglia family...right?

405
00:40:53,860 --> 00:40:57,700
I think you and I can do business.

406
00:40:59,460 --> 00:41:02,020
I need someone strong like you.

407
00:41:02,620 --> 00:41:05,340
I heard you are not happy...

408
00:41:05,740 --> 00:41:07,940
...with the Corleone family.

409
00:41:08,660 --> 00:41:10,340
Want to join me?

410
00:41:11,460 --> 00:41:13,340
What's in it for me?

411
00:41:15,860 --> 00:41:18,660
$50 ,000 to start with.

412
00:41:20,580 --> 00:41:21,780
Not bad!

413
00:41:23,380 --> 00:41:24,940
Agreed?

414
00:41:41,860 --> 00:41:43,460
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

415
00:41:47,700 --> 00:41:48,980
(GRUNTING)

416
00:41:54,740 --> 00:41:55,940
(CHOKING)

417
00:41:58,420 --> 00:41:59,620
(GASPING)

418
00:42:21,940 --> 00:42:25,500
Tom! Tom Hagen. Merry Christmas.

419
00:42:25,620 --> 00:42:30,340
-Glad to see you. I want to talk to you.
-I haven't got time.

420
00:42:30,420 --> 00:42:33,340
Make time, Consigliere. Get in the car.

421
00:42:35,100 --> 00:42:39,460
What are you worried about? If I wanted
to kill you, you'd be dead already.

422
00:42:39,540 --> 00:42:40,900
Get in.

423
00:42:51,460 --> 00:42:55,020
-Fredo,  going to buy some fruit.
-Okay, Pop.

424
00:43:01,540 --> 00:43:04,260
Merry Christmas. I want some fruit.

425
00:44:02,820 --> 00:44:03,820
(WHI MPERING)

426
00:44:20,740 --> 00:44:21,820
(SHOUTING)

427
00:44:24,100 --> 00:44:25,580
(BELL TOLLING)

428
00:44:28,220 --> 00:44:32,100
Would you like me better
if I were a nun? Like in the story.

429
00:44:35,100 --> 00:44:36,100
No.

430
00:44:36,180 --> 00:44:40,340
-What if I were Ingrid Bergman?
-Now, that's a thought.

431
00:44:42,820 --> 00:44:44,740
Michael.

432
00:44:44,820 --> 00:44:48,020
No, I wouldn't like you better
if you were Ingrid Bergman.

433
00:44:48,100 --> 00:44:49,300
What's the matter?

434
00:45:05,100 --> 00:45:07,660
They don't say if he's dead or alive.

435
00:45:14,620 --> 00:45:16,060
(HORN BLARING)

436
00:45:29,020 --> 00:45:32,180
<i>-Sonny, it's Michael.
-Where have you been?</i>

437
00:45:32,260 --> 00:45:34,900
<i>-Is he all right?
-We don't know yet.</i>

438
00:45:34,980 --> 00:45:38,860
<i>There are all kinds of stories.
He was hit bad, Mikey.</i>

439
00:45:40,740 --> 00:45:43,900
<i> -Are you there?
-Yeah,  here.</i>

440
00:45:44,020 --> 00:45:48,700
<i> -Where have you been? I was worried.
-Didn't Tom tell you I called?</i>

441
00:45:48,780 --> 00:45:52,620
<i>No. Look, come home, kid.
You should be with Mama, you hear?</i>

442
00:45:59,780 --> 00:46:01,300
SANDRA: Oh, my God.

443
00:46:03,020 --> 00:46:04,020
(CLATTERING)

444
00:46:04,100 --> 00:46:05,100
(GASPING)

445
00:46:05,180 --> 00:46:06,500
Sonny!

446
00:46:06,580 --> 00:46:07,980
(BABY CRYING)

447
00:46:13,060 --> 00:46:14,540
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

448
00:46:15,020 --> 00:46:17,220
Stay back there.

449
00:46:17,300 --> 00:46:19,860
-Who is it?
-Open up, it's Clemenza.

450
00:46:22,180 --> 00:46:25,300
There's more news about your old man.

451
00:46:25,380 --> 00:46:27,460
Word is out that he's already dead.

452
00:46:27,860 --> 00:46:31,620
-What's the matter with you?
-Take it easy!

453
00:46:31,780 --> 00:46:34,940
-Where was Paulie?
-Sick. He's been sick all winter.

454
00:46:35,020 --> 00:46:37,340
-How often?
-Only three, four times.

455
00:46:37,420 --> 00:46:41,060
-Freddy didn't want a new bodyguard.
-Pick him up now.

456
00:46:41,140 --> 00:46:45,740
I don't care how sick he is. Bring him
to my father's house right now.

457
00:46:45,820 --> 00:46:48,780
-You want anyone sent over here?
-No. Go ahead.

458
00:46:49,300 --> 00:46:50,700
(BABY CRYING)

459
00:46:57,580 --> 00:46:59,980
going to have a couple of our people
come over to the house.

460
00:47:00,060 --> 00:47:01,700
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

461
00:47:04,220 --> 00:47:06,340
<i>-Hello?
-SOLLOZZO: Santino Corleone?</i>

462
00:47:06,420 --> 00:47:09,100
<i>-Yeah.
-We have Tom Hagen.</i>

463
00:47:09,180 --> 00:47:12,740
<i>In three hours he'll be released
with our proposition.</i>

464
00:47:12,820 --> 00:47:16,060
<i>Listen to what he has to say
before you do anything.</i>

465
00:47:16,140 --> 00:47:20,580
<i>What's done is done. Don't lose that
famous temper of yours, Sonny.</i>

466
00:47:20,660 --> 00:47:22,260
I'll wait.

467
00:47:22,340 --> 00:47:23,860
<i>(HANGS UP)</i>

468
00:47:35,900 --> 00:47:37,820
SOLLOZZO: Your boss is dead.

469
00:47:40,700 --> 00:47:44,940
I know you're not in the muscle end
of the family, so don't be scared.

470
00:47:45,980 --> 00:47:49,700
I want you to help the Corleones
and me.

471
00:47:53,500 --> 00:47:57,820
We got him outside his office
about an hour after we picked you up.

472
00:47:59,180 --> 00:48:00,420
Drink it.

473
00:48:04,980 --> 00:48:08,260
It's up to you to make peace
between me and Sonny.

474
00:48:12,340 --> 00:48:14,980
Sonny was hot for my deal, wasn't he?

475
00:48:16,340 --> 00:48:19,060
And you knew
it was the right thing to do.

476
00:48:20,180 --> 00:48:25,020
-Sonny will come after you.
-That will be his first reaction, sure.

477
00:48:26,420 --> 00:48:32,700
So you have to talk sense into him.
The Tattaglia family is behind me.

