but don't look away either.

708
01:13:39,420 --> 01:13:42,780
They'll be scared stiff,
so don't worry about nothing.

709
01:13:44,740 --> 01:13:48,820
You'll be all right. You'll take a vacation,
nobody knows where,

710
01:13:48,900 --> 01:13:50,860
and we'll catch the hell.

711
01:13:51,460 --> 01:13:55,140
-How bad do you think it will be?
-Pretty goddamn bad.

712
01:13:55,260 --> 01:13:58,180
All the other families will probably
line up against us.

713
01:13:58,300 --> 01:14:03,620
These things have to happen every five,
10 years. Gets rid of the bad blood.

714
01:14:03,740 --> 01:14:07,980
Been 10 years since the last one.
You have to stop them at the beginning.

715
01:14:08,100 --> 01:14:13,540
Like they should have stopped Hitler in
Munich, not letting him get away with it.

716
01:14:14,940 --> 01:14:19,260
You know, Mike, we were all proud
of you. Being a hero and all.

717
01:14:19,340 --> 01:14:20,940
Your father too.

718
01:14:29,540 --> 01:14:30,620
(CLICKS)

719
01:14:57,500 --> 01:15:00,740
Nothing. Not a hint. Absolutely nothing.

720
01:15:01,700 --> 01:15:05,740
Even Sollozzo's people don't know
where the meeting will be held.

721
01:15:05,860 --> 01:15:08,100
How much time do we have?

722
01:15:08,900 --> 01:15:13,540
They're going to pick you up outside
Jack Dempsey's in an hour and a half.

723
01:15:14,500 --> 01:15:17,220
CLEMENZA: We could
put a tail on them.

724
01:15:17,340 --> 01:15:19,140
Sollozzo would lose our ass.

725
01:15:20,460 --> 01:15:24,900
-What about the negotiator?
-He's playing pinochle with my men.

726
01:15:25,020 --> 01:15:29,860
-He's happy. They're letting him win.
-Too risky. Maybe we should call it off.

727
01:15:29,980 --> 01:15:33,180
The negotiator plays cards
until Mike is back safe.

728
01:15:33,260 --> 01:15:37,100
-He could blast whoever is in the car.
-CLEMENZA: They'll expect that.

729
01:15:37,220 --> 01:15:39,340
Sollozzo might not even be
in the car , Sonny!

730
01:15:39,460 --> 01:15:40,420
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

731
01:15:40,540 --> 01:15:41,900
I'll get it.

732
01:16:06,180 --> 01:16:08,260
Louis' restaurant in the Bronx.

733
01:16:08,380 --> 01:16:11,540
-Is it reliable?
-My man in McCluskey's precinct.

734
01:16:11,660 --> 01:16:17,100
A police captain is on call 24 hours
a day. He'll be there between 8 and 10.

735
01:16:17,220 --> 01:16:21,860
-Anybody know this joint?
-Sure, I do. It's perfect for us.

736
01:16:21,980 --> 01:16:26,700
A small family place, good food.
Everyone minds his business. Perfect.

737
01:16:27,460 --> 01:16:32,420
They've got an old -fashioned toilet.
You know, the box and the chain thing.

738
01:16:34,340 --> 01:16:37,300
We might be able to
tape the gun behind it.

739
01:16:37,380 --> 01:16:41,340
All right. Mike, you go to the restaurant,

740
01:16:41,420 --> 01:16:45,140
you eat, talk for a while, you relax.
Make them relax.

741
01:16:45,220 --> 01:16:50,340
Then you go to take a leak. No,
better still, you ask permission to go.

742
01:16:50,460 --> 01:16:54,660
Then you come back blasting.
Two shots in the head apiece.

743
01:16:56,380 --> 01:16:58,780
I want somebody very good
to plant that gun.

744
01:16:58,860 --> 01:17:02,180
I don't want him coming out
with just his dick.

745
01:17:02,300 --> 01:17:07,620
-The gun will be there.
-You drive him and pick him up.

746
01:17:07,740 --> 01:17:09,260
Let's move.

747
01:17:14,540 --> 01:17:17,580
Did he tell you to drop the gun
right away?

748
01:17:17,700 --> 01:17:19,460
Yeah, a million times.

749
01:17:24,060 --> 01:17:28,100
Don't forget. Two shots apiece
in the head as soon as you come out.

750
01:17:34,380 --> 01:17:37,860
How long do you think it will be
before I can come back?

751
01:17:38,660 --> 01:17:40,660
At least a year.

752
01:17:40,780 --> 01:17:45,380
I'll square it with Mom, that you're not
seeing her before you leave and...

753
01:17:46,820 --> 01:17:50,500
I'll get a message to that girlfriend
when the time is right.

754
01:17:56,100 --> 01:17:57,540
Take care.

755
01:18:00,260 --> 01:18:01,900
Take care, Mike.

756
01:18:33,380 --> 01:18:37,060
glad you came. I hope
we can straighten everything out.

757
01:18:38,180 --> 01:18:43,140
It's not the way I wanted things to go.
It should never have happened.

758
01:18:43,260 --> 01:18:47,300
I want to straighten everything out.
I don't want my father bothered again.

759
01:18:47,420 --> 01:18:50,500
I swear on my children
that he won't be, Mike.

760
01:18:51,460 --> 01:18:54,660
But you have to keep an open mind
when we talk.

761
01:18:54,780 --> 01:18:58,980
I hope you're not a hothead like Sonny.
You can't talk business with him.

762
01:18:59,100 --> 01:19:00,700
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

763
01:19:00,780 --> 01:19:02,340
McCLUSKEY: He's a good kid.

764
01:19:06,300 --> 01:19:09,540
sorry about the other night, Mike.

765
01:19:09,660 --> 01:19:13,540
I've got to frisk you, so turn around.
On your knees, facing me.

766
01:19:18,460 --> 01:19:22,940
I guess  getting too old for my job.
Too grouchy.

767
01:19:24,260 --> 01:19:27,940
Can't stand the aggravation.
You know how it is.

768
01:19:30,180 --> 01:19:31,500
He's clean.

769
01:19:57,060 --> 01:19:59,180
Going to Jersey?

770
01:20:01,580 --> 01:20:03,140
Maybe.

771
01:20:18,820 --> 01:20:20,260
(HORNS BLARING)

772
01:20:27,300 --> 01:20:29,060
Nice work, Lou.

773
01:21:04,700 --> 01:21:10,020
-How's the food in this restaurant?
-Try the veal. It's the best in the city.

774
01:21:10,140 --> 01:21:11,660
McCLUSKEY: I'll have it.

775
01:21:12,740 --> 01:21:14,340
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

776
01:21:45,820 --> 01:21:48,900
- going to speak Italian to Mikey.
-Go ahead.

777
01:21:54,980 --> 01:21:56,740
(BOTH SPEAKING ITALIAN)

778
01:23:05,220 --> 01:23:06,820
What I want...

779
01:23:07,780 --> 01:23:09,860
What's most important to me

780
01:23:12,420 --> 01:23:16,500
is that I have a guarantee.
No more attempts on my father's life.

781
01:23:16,580 --> 01:23:21,140
What guarantees can I give you?
the hunted one!

782
01:23:21,220 --> 01:23:24,660
I missed my chance.
You think too much of me, kid.

783
01:23:24,740 --> 01:23:26,500
not that clever.

784
01:23:27,940 --> 01:23:30,100
All I want is a truce.

785
01:23:36,340 --> 01:23:40,020
I have to go to the bathroom.
Is it all right?

786
01:23:41,380 --> 01:23:43,780
When you got to go, you got to go.

787
01:23:49,020 --> 01:23:50,900
He's clean.

788
01:23:50,980 --> 01:23:52,980
Don't take too long.

789
01:23:55,940 --> 01:23:57,660
I've frisked a thousand punks.

790
01:24:32,540 --> 01:24:34,100
(TOI LET FLUSHING)

791
01:25:10,780 --> 01:25:12,700
(SOLLOZZO SPEAKING ITALIAN)

792
01:25:45,300 --> 01:25:46,500
(CHOKING)

793
01:27:37,540 --> 01:27:39,380
(CHATTERING)

794
01:28:17,220 --> 01:28:18,700
(SI REN WAI LING)

795
01:28:36,460 --> 01:28:38,340
Okay, you take over.

796
01:28:41,140 --> 01:28:42,940
(ALL CHATTERING)

797
01:28:54,940 --> 01:28:56,700
I love you, Grandpa.

798
01:28:56,820 --> 01:28:58,220
(BABY CRYING)

799
01:28:59,460 --> 01:29:02,100
CONNIE:  sorry, Pa.
He doesn't know you yet.

800
01:29:06,460 --> 01:29:12,460
" I hope you get well, Grandpa, and wish
I see you soon. Your grandson Frank. "

801
01:29:15,300 --> 01:29:17,540
Go with your mother.

802
01:29:17,620 --> 01:29:19,660
Take them downstairs.

803
01:29:25,500 --> 01:29:27,460
Go on, Carlo, you too.

804
01:29:29,140 --> 01:29:30,780
Go on.

805
01:29:33,940 --> 01:29:35,740
(ALL CHATTERING)

806
01:29:50,500 --> 01:29:54,340
-What's the matter with you, Carlo?
-Shut up and set the table.

807
01:30:09,300 --> 01:30:15,100
Since McCluskey's killing, the police
have cracked down on our operations.

808
01:30:16,740 --> 01:30:21,460
And also the other families.
There's been a lot of bad blood.

809
01:30:21,540 --> 01:30:24,860
They hit us, so we hit them back.

810
01:30:25,660 --> 01:30:30,060
Through our newspaper contacts
we've been able to put out material

811
01:30:30,140 --> 01:30:34,260
about McCluskey's link with Sollozzo
in the drug rackets.

812
01:30:34,340 --> 01:30:36,380
So things are loosening up.

813
01:30:37,580 --> 01:30:42,140
And  sending Fredo to Las Vegas,

814
01:30:42,220 --> 01:30:44,660
under the protection
of Don Francesco of L.A.

815
01:30:44,780 --> 01:30:49,100
-I want him to rest.
- going to learn the casino business.

816
01:30:57,060 --> 01:30:58,780
(SOFTLY) Where's Michael?

817
01:31:10,620 --> 01:31:13,620
It was Michael who killed Sollozzo.

818
01:31:15,340 --> 01:31:19,020
But he's safe. We're starting to work
to bring him back.

819
01:31:39,540 --> 01:31:41,820
I want you to find out
where that old pimp Tattaglia is hiding.

820
01:31:41,900 --> 01:31:43,780
I want him now.

821
01:31:43,860 --> 01:31:47,260
Sonny, things are starting to loosen up.

822
01:31:47,340 --> 01:31:51,860
If you go after Tattaglia, all hell
will break loose. Pop can negotiate.

823
01:31:51,940 --> 01:31:57,700
-He must get better first. I'll decide...
-War is costly. We can't do business.

824
01:31:57,780 --> 01:32:01,460
-Neither can they. Don't worry about it!
-We can't afford a stalemate.

825
01:32:01,580 --> 01:32:06,340
-No more stalemate. I'll kill the bastard!
-You're getting a great reputation!

826
01:32:06,420 --> 01:32:12,220
Do as I say! If I had a Sicilian wartime
consigliere. I wouldn't be in this shape!

827
01:32:12,300 --> 01:32:14,460
Pop had Genco. Look what I got.

828
01:32:17,940 --> 01:32:20,140
sorry. I didn't mean that.

829
01:32:21,220 --> 01:32:24,060
Ma made a little dinner. It's Sunday.

830
01:32:24,980 --> 01:32:29,180
Niggers are having a good time
with our policy banks in Harlem.

831
01:32:29,260 --> 01:32:33,260
Driving new Cadillacs,
paying 50% on a bet.

832
01:32:33,340 --> 01:32:36,540
That's because
they've started making big money.

833
01:32:36,620 --> 01:32:39,780
Papa never talked business
at the table.

834
01:32:39,860 --> 01:32:43,580
-CARLO: Shut up, Connie...
-Don't you ever tell her to shut up.

835
01:32:44,300 --> 01:32:45,300
Don't interfere.

836
01:32:47,540 --> 01:32:51,300
I'd like to talk to you after dinner.
I could do more for the family...

837
01:32:51,380 --> 01:32:54,060
We don't discuss business at the table.

838
01:33:31,380 --> 01:33:32,620
(HORN HONKS)

839
01:33:39,340 --> 01:33:41,820
(IN ITALIAN)
I kiss your hand, Don Tommasino.

840
01:33:47,180 --> 01:33:49,100
Why are you so far
from the house?

841
01:33:49,700 --> 01:33:52,300
You know  responsible to your
father for your life.

842
01:33:52,380 --> 01:33:53,620
The bodyguards are here.

843
01:33:54,460 --> 01:33:55,740
It's still dangerous...

844
01:33:56,860 --> 01:33:58,540
We've heard from Santino
in New York...

845
01:33:59,900 --> 01:34:02,020
Your enemies know you're here.

846
01:34:03,980 --> 01:34:05,660
Did Santino say when
I can go back?

847
01:34:08,180 --> 01:34:09,940
It's out of the question.

848
01:34:13,260 --> 01:34:14,620
Where are you going now?

849
01:34:16,180 --> 01:34:17,220
To Corleone.

850
01:34:17,820 --> 01:34:19,020
Take my car.

851
01:34:22,220 --> 01:34:23,220
I want to walk.

852
01:34:25,700 --> 01:34:26,820
Be careful.

853
01:34:40,940 --> 01:34:42,380
(BELL TOLLING)

854
01:34:46,300 --> 01:34:47,900
Michael. Corleone.

855
01:34:59,940 --> 01:35:01,300
(IN ITALIAN)
Where have all the men gone?

856
01:35:02,300 --> 01:35:04,420
They're all dead from vendettas.

857
01:35:05,980 --> 01:35:08,260
There are the names of the dead.

858
01:35:24,020 --> 01:35:27,980
Hey, hey, take me to the America, G. I. !

859
01:35:28,060 --> 01:35:32,180
Hey, hey, take me to the America, G. I. !
Clark Gable!

860
01:35:32,300 --> 01:35:37,340
America! Take me to the America, G. I. !
Clark Gable, Rita Hayworth!

861
01:35:37,620 --> 01:35:39,380
(GRUMBLING IN ITALIAN)

862
01:35:40,900 --> 01:35:42,340
(WOMEN SINGING)

863
01:35:54,500 --> 01:35:56,500
(IN ITALIAN) Mamma mia what a beauty.

864
01:35:56,580 --> 01:35:58,180
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

865
01:36:04,340 --> 01:36:07,260
I think you got hit
by the thunderbolt.

866
01:36:13,220 --> 01:36:17,060
(IN ITALIAN) In Sicily women are more
dangerous than shotguns.

867
01:36:28,460 --> 01:36:30,100
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

868
01:36:38,820 --> 01:36:40,860
Did you have a good hunt?

869
01:36:41,820 --> 01:36:44,060
You know all the girls
around here?

870
01:36:44,580 --> 01:36:46,020
We saw some real beauties.

871
01:36:46,780 --> 01:36:50,140
One of them struck our friend
like a thunderbolt.

872
01:36:53,260 --> 01:36:55,900
She would tempt the devil himself.

873
01:36:57,340 --> 01:36:58,860
