1001
01:54:58,500 --> 01:55:01,260
<i>Consigliere of mine,</i>

1002
01:55:01,380 --> 01:55:04,700
tell your Don
what everyone seems to know.

1003
01:55:04,780 --> 01:55:07,060
I didn't tell Mama anything.

1004
01:55:07,980 --> 01:55:11,140
I was about to come up and wake you
and tell you.

1005
01:55:14,500 --> 01:55:16,580
But you needed a drink first.

1006
01:55:18,820 --> 01:55:20,020
Yeah.

1007
01:55:23,180 --> 01:55:25,580
Well, now you've had your drink.

1008
01:55:30,900 --> 01:55:34,660
They shot Sonny on the causeway.
He's dead.

1009
01:55:50,980 --> 01:55:53,420
I want no inquiries made.

1010
01:55:57,700 --> 01:56:00,140
I want no acts of vengeance.

1011
01:56:01,780 --> 01:56:04,500
I want you to arrange a meeting

1012
01:56:05,460 --> 01:56:07,980
with the heads of the five families.

1013
01:56:09,860 --> 01:56:11,820
This war stops now.

1014
01:56:32,900 --> 01:56:35,300
Call Bonasera.

1015
01:56:35,420 --> 01:56:37,500
I need him now.

1016
01:56:49,380 --> 01:56:54,300
This is Tom Hagen.  calling
for Vito Corleone, at his request.

1017
01:56:54,380 --> 01:56:56,700
You owe your Don a service.

1018
01:56:56,780 --> 01:57:00,220
<i>He has no doubt that you will repay it.</i>

1019
01:57:00,300 --> 01:57:04,420
<i>He will be at your funeral parlor
in one hour. Be there to greet him.</i>

1020
01:57:24,740 --> 01:57:29,340
Well, my friend, are you ready
to do me this service?

1021
01:57:29,420 --> 01:57:32,420
Yes. What do you want me to do?

1022
01:57:40,420 --> 01:57:44,740
I want you to use all your powers
and all your skills.

1023
01:57:48,740 --> 01:57:51,500
I don't want his mother
to see him this way.

1024
01:58:06,940 --> 01:58:09,860
Look how they massacred my boy.

1025
01:58:20,220 --> 01:58:22,020
(BOTH SPEAKING ITALIAN)

1026
01:58:30,140 --> 01:58:31,780
(APOLLONIA LAUGHING)

1027
01:58:36,700 --> 01:58:37,660
(BOTH SPEAKING ITALIAN)

1028
01:58:37,740 --> 01:58:40,900
It's safer to teach you English!

1029
01:58:41,540 --> 01:58:42,940
I know English...

1030
01:58:43,020 --> 01:58:47,620
Monday, Tuesday, Thursday,
Wednesday, Friday, Sunday, Saturday.

1031
01:58:54,500 --> 01:58:56,260
Greetings, Don Tommasino.

1032
01:58:56,900 --> 01:58:58,820
How are things in Palermo?

1033
01:59:04,620 --> 01:59:08,540
Michael is teaching me to
drive...watch, I'll show you.

1034
01:59:11,140 --> 01:59:12,900
How are things in Palermo?

1035
01:59:13,340 --> 01:59:16,300
Young people don't respect
anything anymore...

1036
01:59:17,340 --> 01:59:20,580
times are changing for the worse.

1037
01:59:22,700 --> 01:59:26,020
This place has become
too dangerous for you.

1038
01:59:28,580 --> 01:59:33,580
I want you to move to a villa
near Siracusa...right now.

1039
01:59:39,300 --> 01:59:40,420
What's wrong?

1040
01:59:41,540 --> 01:59:43,620
Bad news from America.

1041
01:59:46,020 --> 01:59:49,580
Your brother , Santino,
they killed him.

1042
01:59:53,100 --> 01:59:54,500
(CAR HONKING)

1043
01:59:55,900 --> 01:59:57,660
Let's go...you promised.

1044
02:00:15,660 --> 02:00:16,660
Fabrizio!

1045
02:00:16,740 --> 02:00:18,060
(IN ITALIAN) Get the car.

1046
02:00:19,420 --> 02:00:23,380
Are you driving yourself, Boss?
Is your wife coming with you?

1047
02:00:23,460 --> 02:00:26,900
No, take her to her father's house
until things are safe.

1048
02:00:26,980 --> 02:00:28,860
Okay, anything you say.

1049
02:00:34,540 --> 02:00:36,220
(IN ITALIAN) Calo, where is Apollonia?

1050
02:00:36,900 --> 02:00:40,300
She's going to surprise you.
She wants to drive.

1051
02:00:42,500 --> 02:00:44,460
She'll make a good American wife.

1052
02:00:45,860 --> 02:00:48,260
Wait, I'll get the baggage.

1053
02:00:58,140 --> 02:01:00,180
Fabrizio!

1054
02:01:00,260 --> 02:01:01,900
(IN ITALIAN) Where are you going?

1055
02:01:02,020 --> 02:01:03,340
(CAR HONKING)

1056
02:01:03,500 --> 02:01:05,820
Wait there! I'll drive to you.

1057
02:01:11,740 --> 02:01:13,180
No, Apollonia!

1058
02:01:35,180 --> 02:01:40,780
VITO: Don Barzini, I want to thank you
for helping me organize this meeting,

1059
02:01:40,900 --> 02:01:45,540
and the other heads of the five families
from New York and New Jersey.

1060
02:01:47,260 --> 02:01:50,260
Carmine Cuneo from the Bronx,

1061
02:01:50,340 --> 02:01:53,500
and from Brooklyn

1062
02:01:55,100 --> 02:01:57,060
Philip Tattaglia.

1063
02:01:58,780 --> 02:02:01,380
And from Staten Island

1064
02:02:01,500 --> 02:02:04,820
we have with us Victor Strachi.

1065
02:02:04,900 --> 02:02:10,300
And the other associates that came as
far as from California and Kansas City

1066
02:02:10,420 --> 02:02:13,980
and all the other territories
of the country. Thank you.

1067
02:02:20,540 --> 02:02:23,860
How did things ever get so far?

1068
02:02:23,940 --> 02:02:25,500
I don't know.

1069
02:02:27,460 --> 02:02:30,820
It was so unfortunate, so unnecessary.

1070
02:02:33,820 --> 02:02:37,140
Tattaglia lost a son, and I lost a son.

1071
02:02:39,460 --> 02:02:42,740
We're quits. And if Tattaglia agrees,

1072
02:02:42,820 --> 02:02:46,660
then  willing to let things go on
as before.

1073
02:02:51,620 --> 02:02:56,820
We all know him as a man of his word.
A modest man who listens to reason.

1074
02:02:56,900 --> 02:03:00,820
Yes, Don Barzini. He's too modest.

1075
02:03:00,900 --> 02:03:04,900
He had all the judges and politicians
in his pocket.

1076
02:03:05,020 --> 02:03:07,780
He refused to share them.

1077
02:03:07,860 --> 02:03:11,460
When did I ever refuse
an accommodation?

1078
02:03:11,580 --> 02:03:13,820
All of you know me.

1079
02:03:14,740 --> 02:03:19,700
When did I ever refuse,
except one time? And why?

1080
02:03:21,300 --> 02:03:26,900
Because I believe this drug business
will destroy us in the years to come.

1081
02:03:26,980 --> 02:03:31,060
It's not like gambling or liquor
or even women,

1082
02:03:31,140 --> 02:03:36,860
which is something that most people
want, but is forbidden by the Church.

1083
02:03:36,980 --> 02:03:41,460
Even the police that have helped us in
the past with gambling and other things

1084
02:03:41,540 --> 02:03:45,620
are going to refuse to help us
when it comes to narcotics.

1085
02:03:45,700 --> 02:03:50,580
I believed that then
and I believe that now.

1086
02:03:50,660 --> 02:03:52,780
Times have changed.

1087
02:03:52,900 --> 02:03:57,460
It's not like the old days,
when we could do anything we wanted.

1088
02:03:57,540 --> 02:04:00,260
A refusal is not the act of a friend.

1089
02:04:00,380 --> 02:04:05,540
If Don Corleone had all the judges and
politicians, then he must share them

1090
02:04:05,660 --> 02:04:10,020
or let others use them. He must let us
draw the water from the well.

1091
02:04:11,060 --> 02:04:14,500
Certainly he can present a bill
for such services.

1092
02:04:14,620 --> 02:04:17,060
After all, we're not communists.

1093
02:04:20,060 --> 02:04:23,020
I also don't believe in drugs.

1094
02:04:23,140 --> 02:04:27,780
For years I paid my people extra, so
they wouldn't do that kind of business.

1095
02:04:27,900 --> 02:04:30,900
Somebody says to them
" I have powders. "

1096
02:04:30,980 --> 02:04:34,340
" If you put up
3 -4,000 dollar investment,

1097
02:04:34,460 --> 02:04:36,820
we can make 50 ,000 distributing. "

1098
02:04:38,180 --> 02:04:43,940
They can't resist. I want to control it
as a business, keep it respectable.

1099
02:04:44,020 --> 02:04:48,580
I don't want it near schools,
I don't want it sold to children.

1100
02:04:48,700 --> 02:04:50,420
<i>That's an infàmia.</i>

1101
02:04:51,700 --> 02:04:55,460
In my city we would keep the traffic
to the colored.

1102
02:04:55,540 --> 02:04:58,580
They're animals,
so let them lose their souls.

1103
02:05:04,900 --> 02:05:08,380
I hoped that we could come here
and reason together.

1104
02:05:09,700 --> 02:05:16,100
And  willing to do whatever is
necessary to find a peaceful solution.

1105
02:05:16,660 --> 02:05:20,980
We are agreed. The traffic in drugs
will be permitted, but controlled.

1106
02:05:21,060 --> 02:05:25,220
Don Corleone will give us protection
in the east, and there will be peace.

1107
02:05:25,340 --> 02:05:28,900
I must have strict assurance
from Corleone.

1108
02:05:29,020 --> 02:05:32,180
As time goes by
and his position becomes stronger ,

1109
02:05:32,260 --> 02:05:34,740
will he attempt any individual vendetta?

1110
02:05:34,820 --> 02:05:39,780
BARZINI : We are all reasonable men.
We don't have to give assurances.

1111
02:05:39,900 --> 02:05:42,660
You talk about vengeance.

1112
02:05:42,740 --> 02:05:45,860
Will vengeance
bring your son back to you?

1113
02:05:45,940 --> 02:05:48,340
Or my boy to me?

1114
02:05:48,420 --> 02:05:51,100
I forgo the vengeance of my son.

1115
02:05:53,780 --> 02:05:56,020
But I have selfish reasons.

1116
02:05:58,180 --> 02:06:01,620
My youngest son was forced
to leave this country

1117
02:06:03,420 --> 02:06:05,860
because of this Sollozzo business.

1118
02:06:07,380 --> 02:06:11,060
And I have to make arrangements
to bring him back here safely.

1119
02:06:11,140 --> 02:06:13,700
Cleared of all these false charges.

1120
02:06:15,100 --> 02:06:18,140
But  a superstitious man.

1121
02:06:18,260 --> 02:06:23,300
If an unlucky accident should befall him,
if he should be shot by a police officer¤,

1122
02:06:24,660 --> 02:06:28,100
or if he should hang himself
in his jail cell,

1123
02:06:28,180 --> 02:06:30,900
or if he's struck by a bolt of lightning,

1124
02:06:32,100 --> 02:06:35,580
then  going to blame
some of the people in this room.

1125
02:06:37,180 --> 02:06:39,420
And that I do not forgive.

1126
02:06:41,780 --> 02:06:44,060
But, that aside

1127
02:06:46,980 --> 02:06:49,300
let me say that I swear

1128
02:06:50,820 --> 02:06:53,820
on the souls of my grandchildren,

1129
02:06:53,940 --> 02:06:58,100
that I will not be the one to break
the peace we've made here today.

1130
02:07:22,580 --> 02:07:27,820
Should I insist that all of Tattaglia's
drug middlemen have clean records?

1131
02:07:27,900 --> 02:07:29,900
Mention it. Don't insist.

1132
02:07:31,820 --> 02:07:36,540
-Barzini will know without being told.
-You mean Tattaglia.

1133
02:07:38,100 --> 02:07:39,980
Tattaglia's a pimp.

1134
02:07:41,020 --> 02:07:44,020
He could never have outfought Santino.

1135
02:07:46,300 --> 02:07:51,660
But I didn't know until this day
that it was Barzini all along.

1136
02:08:06,500 --> 02:08:08,500
Come on, Nancy.

1137
02:08:09,660 --> 02:08:12,140
Keep together , everyone. Brian.

1138
02:08:13,420 --> 02:08:15,020
Okay, all right.

1139
02:08:27,540 --> 02:08:29,660
How long have you been back?

1140
02:08:30,420 --> 02:08:32,180
I've been back a year.

1141
02:08:33,540 --> 02:08:35,580
Longer than that, I think.

1142
02:08:38,300 --> 02:08:40,380
It's good to see you, Kay.

1143
02:08:50,940 --> 02:08:53,380
working for my father now, Kay.

1144
02:08:55,780 --> 02:08:58,660
He's been sick. Very sick.

1145
02:09:00,140 --> 02:09:02,020
But you're not like him.

1146
02:09:02,100 --> 02:09:05,740
You told me you weren't going to
become like your father.

1147
02:09:07,620 --> 02:09:11,740
My father is no different
than any other powerful man.

1148
02:09:11,820 --> 02:09:15,180
Any man who's responsible
for other people.

1149
02:09:16,300 --> 02:09:18,660
Like a senator or president.

1150
02:09:18,740 --> 02:09:21,100
-How naive you sound.
-Why?

1151
02:09:21,180 --> 02:09:23,860
They don't have men killed.

1152
02:09:26,940 --> 02:09:28,860
Who's being naive, Kay?

1153
02:09:30,100 --> 02:09:34,180
My father's way of doing things is over.
Even he knows that.

1154
02:09:35,660 --> 02:09:39,860
In five years the Corleone family
is going to be completely legitimate.

1155
02:09:41,620 --> 02:09:45,420
Trust me. That's all I can tell you
about my business. Kay...

1156
02:09:46,780 --> 02:09:49,780
Michael, why did you come here? Why?

1157
02:09:51,060 --> 02:09:55,700
What do you want with me after all
this time? I've been calling and writing.

1158
02:09:55,780 --> 02:09:59,140
I came because I need you.
I care for you.

1159
02:09:59,220 --> 02:10:02,900
-Please stop it, Michael.
-Because... I want you to marry me.

1160
02:10:04,500 --> 02:10:07,020
-It's too late.
-Please, Kay...

1161
02:10:08,660 --> 02:10:12,420
I'll do anything you ask
to make up for what's happened to us.

1162
02:10:14,180 --> 02:10:18,260
Because that's important, Kay.
Because what's important is that

1163
02:10:19,740 --> 02:10:22,860
we have each other.
That we have a life together.

1164
02:10:24,380 --> 02:10:26,980
That we have children. Our children.

1165
02:10:28,420 --> 02:10:30,500
Kay, I need you.

1166
02:10:32,380 --> 02:10:33,900
And I love you.

1167
02:10:55,100 --> 02:10:58,740
TESSIO: Barzini's people chisel
my territory and we do nothing about it!

1168
02:10:58,860 --> 02:11:02,340
-Soon I'll have no place to hang my hat!
-M ICHAEL: Be patient.

1169
02:11:02,420 --> 02:11:05,420
TESSIO:  not asking for help.
Just take off the handcuffs.

1170
02:11:05,500 --> 02:11:08,500
M ICHAEL: Be patient.
CARLO: We must protect ourselves.

1171
02:11:08,580 --> 02:11:11,900
-Let me recruit some new men.
-M ICHAEL: No.

1172
02:11:11,980 --> 02:11:15,700
-Barzini would get an excuse to fight.
-TESSIO: Mike, you're wrong.

1173
02:11:17,140 --> 02:11:19,260
CLEMENZA: Don Corleone...

1174
02:11:19,340 --> 02:11:23,260
You once said that one day Tessio
and me could form our own family.

1175
02:11:23,340 --> 02:11:27,220
Till today I would never think of it.
I must ask your permission.

1176
02:11:28,180 --> 02:11:30,780
Michael is now head of the family.

1177
02:11:30,860 --> 02:11:34,940
If he gives his permission,
then you have my blessing.

1178
02:11:35,020 --> 02:11:37,340
After we make the move to Nevada

1179
02:11:37,420 --> 02:11:41,620
you can leave the Corleone family
and go on your own.

1180
02:11:41,700 --> 02:11:45,860
-TESSIO: How long will that be?
-Six months.

1181
02:11:45,940 --> 02:11:49,060
Forgive me, but with you gone,

1182
02:11:49,140 --> 02:11:51,860
me and Pete
will come under Barzini's thumb.

1183
02:11:51,940 --> 02:11:57,380
I hate that Barzini. In six months' time
there will be nothing left to build on.

1184
02:11:57,460 --> 02:12:00,260
-Do you have faith in my judgment?
-Yes.

1185
02:12:00,340 --> 02:12:03,140
-Do I have your loyalty?
-Always, Godfather.

1186
02:12:03,260 --> 02:12:06,380
Then be a friend to Michael.
Do as he says.

1187
02:12:11,060 --> 02:12:16,220
Things are negotiated that'll solve your
problems and answer your questions.

1188
02:12:16,300 --> 02:12:18,500
That's all I can tell you now.

1189
02:12:19,300 --> 02:12:21,820
Carlo, you grew up in Nevada.

1190
02:12:21,900 --> 02:12:25,100
When we make our move there,
you'll be my right -hand man.

1191
02:12:25,180 --> 02:12:29,780
Tom Hagen is no longer consigliere.
He'll be our lawyer in Vegas.

1192
02:12:29,860 --> 02:12:32,300
That's no reflection on Tom,
just how I want it.

1193
02:12:32,380 --> 02:12:36,900
If I ever need help, who's a better
consigliere than my father? That's it.

1194
02:12:56,100 --> 02:12:59,780
-Thank you, Papa.
- happy for you, Carlo.

1195
02:12:59,860 --> 02:13:02,620
Mike... Why am I out?

1196
02:13:04,060 --> 02:13:06,700
You're not a wartime consigliere. Tom.

1197
02:13:07,940 --> 02:13:11,060
Things may get rough with the move.

1198
02:13:11,140 --> 02:13:12,380
Tom.

1199
02:13:17,340 --> 02:13:22,300
I advised Michael. I never thought
you were a bad consigliere.

1200
02:13:22,380 --> 02:13:26,340
I thought Santino was a bad Don,
rest in peace.

1201
02:13:27,740 --> 02:13:30,820
Michael has all my confidence,
just as you do.

1202
02:13:31,740 --> 02:13:36,540
But there are reasons why you must
have no part in what is going to happen.

1203
02:13:37,540 --> 02:13:40,460
-Maybe I could help.
-You're out, Tom.

1204
02:13:50,220 --> 02:13:51,660
(DOOR CLOSING)

1205
02:14:27,700 --> 02:14:31,820
I can't get over the way your face looks.
So good!

1206
02:14:31,940 --> 02:14:36,300
This doctor did some job.
Did Kay talk you into it? Hey, hey, hey!

1207
02:14:36,380 --> 02:14:40,340
Leave them out here.
He's tired and wants to clean up.

1208
02:14:40,420 --> 02:14:42,660
Let me open the door , all right?

1209
02:14:44,020 --> 02:14:46,500
<i>(PLAYING
FOR HE'S A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW)</i>

1210
02:14:48,580 --> 02:14:53,820
-Hello, Mike! Welcome to Las Vegas!
-All for you, kid! It's all his idea.

1211
02:14:53,900 --> 02:14:56,380
JOHNNY: Your brother Freddy.
FREDO: Girls?

1212
02:15:04,300 --> 02:15:07,660
-Anything you want, kid, anything.
-Who are the girls?

1213
02:15:09,020 --> 02:15:12,260
-That's for you to find out.
-Get rid of them, Fredo.

1214
02:15:13,740 --> 02:15:18,220
-Hey, Mike...
- here on business. Get rid of them.

1215
02:15:18,300 --> 02:15:20,860
tired. Get rid of the band too.

1216
02:15:26,500 --> 02:15:29,660
Hey, take off. Take off. Let's go.

1217
02:15:29,740 --> 02:15:31,740
Hey, that's it. Hey, Angelo.

1218
02:15:33,420 --> 02:15:35,420
Hey, come on! Scram!

1219
02:15:37,060 --> 02:15:40,460
Come on, honey. I don't know
what's the matter with him, Johnny.

1220
02:15:40,540 --> 02:15:41,780
Sorry.

1221
02:15:43,660 --> 02:15:46,100
I don't know. He's tired.

1222
02:15:51,460 --> 02:15:52,740
(DOOR CLOSING)

1223
02:15:52,820 --> 02:15:55,780
What happened to Moe Greene?

1224
02:15:55,860 --> 02:16:00,060
He had some business. He said to
give him a call when the party started.

1225
02:16:00,140 --> 02:16:01,980
Well, give him a call.

1226
02:16:03,260 --> 02:16:06,300
-Johnny, how are you?
-Nice to see you, Mike.

1227
02:16:06,380 --> 02:16:08,500
M ICHAEL: We're proud of you.
JOHNNY: Thanks.

1228
02:16:08,580 --> 02:16:12,060
Sit down, I want to talk to you.
The Don is proud too.

1229
02:16:12,140 --> 02:16:14,260
Well, I owe it all to him.

1230
02:16:15,420 --> 02:16:16,940
He knows how grateful you are.

1231
02:16:17,020 --> 02:16:20,140
That's why
he'd like to ask a favor of you.

1232
02:16:20,220 --> 02:16:22,060
Mike, what can I do?

1233
02:16:23,180 --> 02:16:25,540
We're thinking of giving up our interests

1234
02:16:25,620 --> 02:16:28,380
in the olive oil business
and settling here.

1235
02:16:29,180 --> 02:16:34,340
Moe will sell us his share of the casino
and the hotel, so we'll own all of it.

1236
02:16:34,420 --> 02:16:37,060
-Tom!
-Are you sure?

1237
02:16:37,140 --> 02:16:40,020
Moe loves the business.
He never said nothing about selling.

1238
02:16:40,100 --> 02:16:42,700
I'll make him an offer he can't refuse.

1239
02:16:43,900 --> 02:16:46,260
See, Johnny...

1240
02:16:46,340 --> 02:16:50,380
We figure that entertainment
would draw gamblers to the casino.

1241
02:16:50,460 --> 02:16:54,060
We hope you'll sign a contract
to appear five times a year.

1242
02:16:56,860 --> 02:17:01,300
Perhaps convince some of your friends
in the movies to do the same.

1243
02:17:02,500 --> 02:17:04,540
We're counting on you.

1244
02:17:06,460 --> 02:17:09,980
Sure, Mike.
I'll do anything for my godfather.

1245
02:17:10,060 --> 02:17:11,300
Good.

1246
02:17:12,860 --> 02:17:17,300
Hey, Mike! Hello, fellows.
Everybody's here. Freddy, Tom.

1247
02:17:17,380 --> 02:17:19,820
-Good to see you.
-How are you, Moe?

1248
02:17:19,940 --> 02:17:24,820
Have everything? Specially prepared
food, the best dancers, and good credit.

1249
02:17:24,900 --> 02:17:28,340
Draw chips for everybody,
so they can play on the house.

1250
02:17:30,900 --> 02:17:33,500
Is my credit good enough
to buy you out?

1251
02:17:35,220 --> 02:17:36,980
Buy me out?

1252
02:17:37,060 --> 02:17:39,540
The casino, the hotel.

1253
02:17:39,620 --> 02:17:42,420
The Corleone family
wants to buy you out.

1254
02:17:42,500 --> 02:17:47,700
The Corleone family wants
to buy me out? No, I buy you out.

1255
02:17:47,780 --> 02:17:51,060
Your casino loses money.
We can do better.

1256
02:17:51,140 --> 02:17:54,860
-You think  skimming off the top?
-You're unlucky.

1257
02:17:59,420 --> 02:18:01,780
You Guineas make me laugh.

1258
02:18:01,900 --> 02:18:06,300
I took Freddy in when you had a bad
time, and now you try to push me out!

1259
02:18:07,580 --> 02:18:10,940
You did that
because we bankrolled your casino

1260
02:18:16,140 --> 02:18:18,780
Yes. First of all, you're all done.

1261
02:18:18,860 --> 02:18:21,180
You don't have
that kind of muscle anymore.

1262
02:18:21,300 --> 02:18:25,500
The Godfather is sick. You're getting
chased out of New York by the others.

1263
02:18:25,580 --> 02:18:29,340
Do you think you can come to my hotel
and take over?

1264
02:18:29,420 --> 02:18:34,260
I talked to Barzini. I can make a deal
with him and still keep my hotel!

1265
02:18:34,340 --> 02:18:37,700
Is that why you slapped my brother
around in public?

1266
02:18:37,780 --> 02:18:42,420
That was nothing, Mike.
Moe didn't mean nothing by that.

1267
02:18:42,500 --> 02:18:46,540
He flies off the handle sometimes,
but we're good friends.

1268
02:18:46,620 --> 02:18:51,180
I have a business to run.
I've got to kick asses sometimes.

1269
02:18:51,260 --> 02:18:54,980
We had an argument,
so I had to straighten him out.

1270
02:18:55,060 --> 02:18:57,780
You straightened my brother out?

1271
02:18:57,860 --> 02:19:02,140
He was banging cocktail waitresses!
Players couldn't get a drink.

1272
02:19:02,220 --> 02:19:04,060
What's wrong with you?

1273
02:19:08,780 --> 02:19:11,620
I leave for New York tomorrow.
Think about a price.

1274
02:19:11,700 --> 02:19:12,740
(DRINK SPI LLING)

1275
02:19:12,820 --> 02:19:14,220
Son -of-a -bitch!

1276
02:19:14,300 --> 02:19:19,260
Moe Greene! I made my bones
when you were out with cheerleaders.

1277
02:19:19,340 --> 02:19:21,740
Wait a minute, Moe. I have an idea.

1278
02:19:22,780 --> 02:19:26,220
<i>Tom, you're the consigliere.
Talk to the Don...</i>

1279
02:19:26,340 --> 02:19:31,500
Just a minute. Don is semi -retired and
Mike is in charge of the family business.

1280
02:19:31,580 --> 02:19:34,780
If you have anything to say,
say it to Michael.

1281
02:19:37,700 --> 02:19:38,700
(DOOR SLAMM ING)

1282
02:19:39,500 --> 02:19:44,100
Mike, you don't come to Las Vegas and
talk to a man like Moe Greene like that!

1283
02:19:44,820 --> 02:19:45,980
Fredo...

1284
02:19:47,140 --> 02:19:49,780
You're my older brother , and I love you.

1285
02:19:51,180 --> 02:19:55,020
But don't ever take sides with anyone
against the family again.

1286
02:19:56,460 --> 02:19:57,620
Ever.

1287
02:20:05,260 --> 02:20:09,220
I have to see my father and his people,
so have dinner without me.

1288
02:20:10,940 --> 02:20:15,580
This weekend we'll go out. We'll go to
the city, see a show and have dinner.

1289
02:20:22,700 --> 02:20:25,620
Your sister wants to ask you something.

1290
02:20:25,700 --> 02:20:27,740
-Let her ask.
-She's afraid to.

1291
02:20:27,820 --> 02:20:30,660
They want you to be godfather
to their boy.

1292
02:20:30,740 --> 02:20:32,500
-We'll see.
-Will you?

1293
02:20:32,580 --> 02:20:34,780
Let me think about it. Come on.

1294
02:20:43,260 --> 02:20:46,060
Barzini will move against you first.

1295
02:20:46,140 --> 02:20:50,380
He'll set up a meeting with someone
you absolutely trust.

1296
02:20:50,460 --> 02:20:52,420
Guaranteeing your safety.

1297
02:20:53,620 --> 02:20:56,540
And at that meeting
you'll be assassinated.

1298
02:21:01,140 --> 02:21:04,020
I like to drink wine more than I used to.

1299
02:21:05,340 --> 02:21:08,740
-Anyway,  drinking more.
-It's good for you, Pop.

1300
02:21:13,580 --> 02:21:15,020
I don't know.

1301
02:21:16,980 --> 02:21:19,780
Are you happy with your wife
and children?

1302
02:21:20,740 --> 02:21:23,460
-Very happy.
-That's good.

1303
02:21:25,220 --> 02:21:29,900
I hope you don't mind the way I keep
going over this Barzini business.

1304
02:21:30,020 --> 02:21:32,820
-No, not at all.
-It's an old habit.

1305
02:21:34,220 --> 02:21:37,060
I spend my life trying not to be careless.

1306
02:21:38,580 --> 02:21:41,900
Women and children can be careless,
but not men.

1307
02:21:45,060 --> 02:21:47,340
-How's your boy?
-He's good.

1308
02:21:47,460 --> 02:21:50,020
He looks more like you every day.

1309
02:21:52,660 --> 02:21:56,900
He's smarter than I am. He's three
and can read the funny papers.

1310
02:21:58,980 --> 02:22:00,900
Read the funny papers.

1311
02:22:07,860 --> 02:22:13,260
I want you to arrange for a telephone
man to check all in - and out -going calls.

1312
02:22:13,380 --> 02:22:18,500
-I did it already. I took care of that, Pop.
-That's right. I forgot.

1313
02:22:22,340 --> 02:22:23,980
What's the matter?

1314
02:22:24,740 --> 02:22:26,740
What's bothering you?

1315
02:22:30,180 --> 02:22:34,660
I'll handle it. I told you I can handle it,
so I'll handle it.

1316
02:22:47,340 --> 02:22:51,660
I knew that Santino
would have to go through all this.

1317
02:22:51,780 --> 02:22:53,300
And Fredo...

1318
02:22:55,940 --> 02:22:57,860
Fredo was, well...

1319
02:22:59,660 --> 02:23:02,380
But I never wanted this for you.

1320
02:23:04,580 --> 02:23:09,460
I worked my whole life. I don't apologize
for taking care of my family.

1321
02:23:09,540 --> 02:23:13,300
And I refused to be a fool,

1322
02:23:13,380 --> 02:23:17,380
dancing on a string
held by all those big shots.

1323
02:23:19,220 --> 02:23:22,500
I don't apologize. That's my life,
but I thought that,

1324
02:23:24,100 --> 02:23:29,100
that when it was your time, you would
be the one to hold the strings.

1325
02:23:30,820 --> 02:23:36,260
Senator Corleone. Governor Corleone.
Something.

1326
02:23:36,340 --> 02:23:39,220
<i>Another pezzonovante.</i>

1327
02:23:39,300 --> 02:23:40,900
Well...

1328
02:23:43,940 --> 02:23:47,740
Just wasn't enough time, Michael.
Wasn't enough time.

1329
02:23:47,820 --> 02:23:51,180
We'll get there, Pop. We'll get there.

1330
02:23:55,820 --> 02:24:00,100
Now listen, whoever comes to you
with this Barzini meeting,

1331
02:24:00,180 --> 02:24:02,980
he's the traitor. Don't forget that.

1332
02:24:19,300 --> 02:24:21,300
Can I hold it, please?

1333
02:24:35,780 --> 02:24:39,540
-Can I water these?
-Yes, go ahead.

1334
02:24:39,620 --> 02:24:42,260
Over here, over here.

1335
02:24:44,100 --> 02:24:46,500
Be careful. You're spilling it.

1336
02:24:50,180 --> 02:24:51,780
(ANTHONY LAUGHING)

1337
02:24:52,580 --> 02:24:54,260
Anthony!

1338
02:24:54,340 --> 02:24:55,980
Come here, come here.

1339
02:25:00,900 --> 02:25:03,460
That's it. We'll put it right there.

1340
02:25:04,940 --> 02:25:06,180
(SIGHING)

1341
02:25:08,500 --> 02:25:10,980
I'll show you something. Come here.

1342
02:25:12,940 --> 02:25:14,740
Stand there.

1343
02:25:18,340 --> 02:25:20,020
Give me an orange!

1344
02:25:23,140 --> 02:25:24,420
(GROWLING)

1345
02:25:26,380 --> 02:25:27,940
(ANTHONY CRYING)

1346
02:25:28,020 --> 02:25:29,540
(VITO LAUGHING)

1347
02:25:37,620 --> 02:25:39,300
That's a new trick.

1348
02:25:40,300 --> 02:25:42,540
You run in there. Run in there.

1349
02:25:54,420 --> 02:25:55,460
(VITO LAUGHING)

1350
02:25:55,540 --> 02:25:57,380
ANTHONY: Where are you?

1351
02:26:02,540 --> 02:26:03,820
(COUGHING)

1352
02:26:04,940 --> 02:26:06,540
(ANTHONY LAUGHING)

1353
02:26:11,340 --> 02:26:13,060
(COUGHING CONTINUES)

1354
02:26:17,540 --> 02:26:19,140
(ANTHONY LAUGHING)

1355
02:26:26,060 --> 02:26:27,340
(ANTHONY EXCLAI M ING)

1356
02:26:33,140 --> 02:26:34,820
(ANTHONY CHATTERING)

1357
02:26:48,340 --> 02:26:49,780
(BELL TOLLING)

1358
02:28:47,780 --> 02:28:50,060
Mike, can I have a minute?

1359
02:28:59,780 --> 02:29:02,100
Barzini wants to arrange a meeting.

1360
02:29:02,180 --> 02:29:05,380
He says we can straighten out
any of our problems.

1361
02:29:06,020 --> 02:29:08,100
-You talked to him?
-Yeah.

1362
02:29:09,380 --> 02:29:13,060
I can arrange security. On my territory.

1363
02:29:15,980 --> 02:29:18,380
-All right?
-All right.

1364
02:29:35,180 --> 02:29:38,060
Do you know
how they're going to come at you?

1365
02:29:40,460 --> 02:29:43,980
They're arranging a meeting
in Brooklyn. Tessio's ground.

1366
02:29:46,060 --> 02:29:47,780
Where I'll be safe.

1367
02:29:59,500 --> 02:30:02,940
I always thought it would be Clemenza,
not Tessio.

1368
02:30:03,020 --> 02:30:06,700
It's the smart move.
Tessio was always smarter.

1369
02:30:08,820 --> 02:30:10,060
But  going to wait.

1370
02:30:10,700 --> 02:30:11,700
After the baptism.

1371
02:30:15,380 --> 02:30:18,860
I've decided to be godfather
to Connie's baby.

1372
02:30:18,980 --> 02:30:22,900
And then I'll meet
with Don Barzini and Tattaglia.

1373
02:30:24,420 --> 02:30:27,300
All the heads of the five families.

1374
02:30:30,540 --> 02:30:31,980
(ORGAN PLAYING)

1375
02:30:34,860 --> 02:30:36,300
(BABY CRYING)

1376
02:30:52,180 --> 02:30:53,900
(RECITING IN LATIN)

1377
02:31:23,140 --> 02:31:24,780
<i>(RECITING CONTINUES)</i>

1378
02:32:42,500 --> 02:32:45,100
PRI EST: Michael, do you believe in God,
the Father ,

1379
02:32:45,220 --> 02:32:47,300
Creator of Heaven and Earth?

1380
02:32:47,380 --> 02:32:48,460
I do.

1381
02:32:48,580 --> 02:32:51,860
<i>Do you believe in Jesus Christ,
His only Son, our Lord?</i>

1382
02:32:51,940 --> 02:32:52,940
<i>MICHAEL: I do.</i>

1383
02:32:53,060 --> 02:32:56,940
<i>PRIEST: Do you believe in the
Holy Ghost, the Holy Catholic Church?</i>

1384
02:32:57,060 --> 02:32:58,220
<i>MICHAEL: I do.</i>

1385
02:32:58,340 --> 02:33:00,580
<i>(RECITING CONTINUES IN LATIN)</i>

1386
02:33:30,020 --> 02:33:31,380
<i>(BABY CRYING)</i>

1387
02:33:31,500 --> 02:33:33,220
<i>(RECITING CONTINUES)</i>

1388
02:34:01,100 --> 02:34:05,260
PRI EST: Michael Francis Rizzi,
do you renounce Satan?

1389
02:34:11,300 --> 02:34:12,460
I do renounce him.

1390
02:34:21,740 --> 02:34:23,140
And all his works?

1391
02:34:31,180 --> 02:34:32,940
(MUFFLED SHOUTING)

1392
02:34:36,420 --> 02:34:37,420
I do renounce them.

1393
02:34:39,140 --> 02:34:40,300
WOMAN: Oh, God!

1394
02:34:43,140 --> 02:34:46,660
-And all his pomps?
-I do renounce them.

1395
02:35:01,740 --> 02:35:05,780
Michael Rizzi, will you be baptized?

1396
02:35:05,860 --> 02:35:07,060
I will.

1397
02:35:07,220 --> 02:35:08,980
(RECITING IN LATIN)

1398
02:35:13,860 --> 02:35:19,140
Michael Rizzi, go in peace,
and may the Lord be with you. Amen.

1399
02:35:19,780 --> 02:35:21,540
(CHURCH BELLS RINGING)

1400
02:35:24,340 --> 02:35:26,100
(ALL CHATTERING)

1401
02:35:32,780 --> 02:35:34,580
Kay!

1402
02:35:34,660 --> 02:35:36,580
Kiss your godfather.

1403
02:35:47,980 --> 02:35:49,300
(INAUDI BLE)

1404
02:35:59,980 --> 02:36:03,900
Can't go to Vegas.
Something's come up.

1405
02:36:03,980 --> 02:36:05,580
Everybody has to leave without us.

1406
02:36:05,700 --> 02:36:08,500
-CONNIE: Mike, it's our first vacation!
-Connie, please.

1407
02:36:08,620 --> 02:36:11,980
Go back to the house, wait for my call.
It's important.

1408
02:36:13,060 --> 02:36:15,300
I'll only be a couple of days.

1409
02:36:30,980 --> 02:36:33,060
We're on our way to Brooklyn.

1410
02:36:35,140 --> 02:36:38,780
-I hope Mike can get us a good deal.
- sure he will.

1411
02:36:46,220 --> 02:36:51,460
Sal, Tom, the boss says he'll come in a
separate car , so you two go on ahead.

1412
02:36:51,580 --> 02:36:54,900
-That screws up my arrangements.
-That's what he said.

1413
02:36:54,980 --> 02:36:57,060
I can't go either , Sal.

1414
02:37:08,580 --> 02:37:12,260
Tell Mike it was only business.
I always liked him.

1415
02:37:13,900 --> 02:37:16,580
-He understands that.
-Excuse me, Sal.

1416
02:37:22,340 --> 02:37:24,740
Tom, can you get me off the hook?

1417
02:37:25,860 --> 02:37:28,900
-For old times' sake?
-Can't do it, Sally.

1418
02:37:59,140 --> 02:38:00,740
(TELEPHONE BEING DIALLED)

1419
02:38:12,500 --> 02:38:15,140
You have to answer for Santino, Carlo.

1420
02:38:19,900 --> 02:38:23,620
-Mike, you got it all wrong.
-You fingered Sonny for Barzini.

1421
02:38:24,660 --> 02:38:28,340
That little farce
you played with my sister.

1422
02:38:28,420 --> 02:38:33,300
-You think that could fool a Corleone?
- innocent. I swear on the kids.

1423
02:38:33,380 --> 02:38:36,020
-Please, don't do this.
-Sit down.

1424
02:38:38,580 --> 02:38:40,740
Don't do this to me, please.

1425
02:38:49,660 --> 02:38:51,300
Barzini is dead.

1426
02:38:53,340 --> 02:38:55,580
So is Philip Tattaglia.

1427
02:38:56,740 --> 02:38:58,180
Moe Greene.

1428
02:38:59,100 --> 02:39:02,740
Strachi. Cuneo.

1429
02:39:04,580 --> 02:39:09,700
Today I settle all family business,
so don't tell me you're innocent, Carlo.

1430
02:39:09,780 --> 02:39:11,460
Admit what you did.

1431
02:39:15,260 --> 02:39:16,860
Get him a drink.

1432
02:39:22,900 --> 02:39:24,100
Come on.

1433
02:39:25,380 --> 02:39:27,700
Don't be afraid, Carlo.

1434
02:39:27,780 --> 02:39:30,580
Do you think
I'd make my sister a widow?

1435
02:39:31,620 --> 02:39:34,260
godfather to your son, Carlo.

1436
02:39:40,860 --> 02:39:42,820
Go ahead, drink, drink.

1437
02:39:47,420 --> 02:39:51,100
No, you're out of the family business.
That's your punishment.

1438
02:39:52,100 --> 02:39:55,940
You're finished.
putting you on a plane to Vegas.

1439
02:39:56,020 --> 02:39:57,540
Tom.

1440
02:40:01,540 --> 02:40:05,060
I want you to stay there. Understand?

1441
02:40:05,140 --> 02:40:07,580
Only don't tell me you're innocent.

1442
02:40:08,740 --> 02:40:12,860
Because it insults my intelligence.
Makes me very angry.

1443
02:40:16,900 --> 02:40:18,900
Who approached you?

1444
02:40:20,100 --> 02:40:22,260
Tattaglia or Barzini?

1445
02:40:29,820 --> 02:40:31,460
It was Barzini.

1446
02:40:35,420 --> 02:40:36,900
Good.

1447
02:40:42,900 --> 02:40:46,820
There's a car waiting outside
to take you to the airport.

1448
02:40:46,900 --> 02:40:50,260
I'll call your wife
and tell her what flight you're on.

1449
02:40:54,340 --> 02:40:56,820
-Mike...
-Get out of my sight.

1450
02:41:21,860 --> 02:41:23,460
Hello, Carlo.

1451
02:41:26,660 --> 02:41:27,940
(GRUNTING)

1452
02:42:19,180 --> 02:42:20,780
(CONNIE SCREAM ING)

1453
02:42:20,900 --> 02:42:23,860
- trying to tell you...
-CONNIE: Mama, please!

1454
02:42:28,980 --> 02:42:30,100
(SOBBING)

1455
02:42:31,940 --> 02:42:33,860
Michael!

1456
02:42:33,980 --> 02:42:35,940
KAY: What is it?
CONNIE: Where is he?

1457
02:42:38,220 --> 02:42:43,140
Michael, you lousy bastard!
You killed my husband.

1458
02:42:43,260 --> 02:42:47,140
You waited until Papa died,
so nobody could stop you.

1459
02:42:47,220 --> 02:42:50,180
You blamed him for Sonny.
Everybody did.

1460
02:42:50,260 --> 02:42:55,780
But you never thought about me!
Now what are we going to do?

1461
02:42:55,900 --> 02:42:57,460
KAY: Connie.

1462
02:42:59,620 --> 02:43:02,180
CONNIE: Why do you think
he kept Carlo at the Mall?

1463
02:43:02,300 --> 02:43:05,020
He knew he was going to kill him.

1464
02:43:05,100 --> 02:43:10,220
And you stood godfather to our baby.
You lousy cold -hearted bastard!

1465
02:43:10,340 --> 02:43:14,220
Want to know how many men he had
killed with Carlo? Read the papers!

1466
02:43:14,300 --> 02:43:16,940
That's your husband,
that's your husband!

1467
02:43:18,660 --> 02:43:20,300
(CONNIE SPITTING)

1468
02:43:24,100 --> 02:43:25,100
(CONNIE SOBBING)

1469
02:43:26,220 --> 02:43:30,260
No! No, no...

1470
02:43:30,340 --> 02:43:33,540
Take her upstairs. Get her a doctor.

1471
02:43:53,820 --> 02:43:55,500
She's hysterical.

1472
02:43:59,860 --> 02:44:01,540
Hysterical.

1473
02:44:03,460 --> 02:44:05,100
Michael, is it true?

1474
02:44:06,980 --> 02:44:10,540
-Don't ask me about my business, Kay.
-Is it true?

1475
02:44:10,620 --> 02:44:13,220
Don't ask me about my business.
Enough!

1476
02:44:32,500 --> 02:44:33,940
All right.

1477
02:44:36,660 --> 02:44:38,340
This one time.

1478
02:44:42,180 --> 02:44:45,340
This one time
I'll let you ask me about my affairs.

1479
02:44:51,140 --> 02:44:52,540
Is it true?

1480
02:44:56,420 --> 02:44:57,900
Is it?

1481
02:44:59,620 --> 02:45:00,900
No.

1482
02:45:14,300 --> 02:45:17,060
I guess we both need a drink. Come on.

1483
02:45:30,980 --> 02:45:32,540
(GLASS CLINKING)

1484
02:45:47,100 --> 02:45:48,740
Don Corleone.

